history.content:
CS C8 (Data 8): 

This week I confirmed with the instructor that there are no plans to further expand enrollment past 1296. If you are wait listed and wondering if you will get into the class, the general rule of thumb is that 10% of enrolled students will drop - ALTHOUGH THERE ARE NO GUARANTEES that will be the case in this class. IF YOU ARE WAIT LISTED - have a back up plan in case you cannot get into the class.

CS 170: Appx 200 more seats have been made available in this class. During phase 2 they are restricted to EECS majors but when the adjustment period begins on August 13th, that restriction will come down and the wait list will AUTOMATICALLY fill open seats with people from the wait list based on wait list position.

Also for CS 170 - the final date has been changed to avoid a conflict with the final date for CS 188. See @7327 for more information.
